# Re-include the gateway test sources — the bare `test/` rule above was a
# carry-over from a deleted top-level scratch dir and was never intended to
# block real Maven test trees. The negation pattern makes the intent
# explicit (and survives anyone re-adding similar rules later).
!java/gateway_node/src/test/
!java/gateway_node/src/test/**

# Same story for tools/scripts/ — the bare `scripts/` rule was meant for a
# deleted scratch directory, but tools/scripts/ has 10+ tracked .ps1/.sh
# files already (added one by one with `git add -f`). The negation makes
# `git add tools/scripts/foo.sh` work without -f and prevents future
# scripts from silently going un-tracked.
!tools/scripts/
!tools/scripts/**

# Re-include Go module files. The wildcard `*.mod` rule near the top of
# this file was meant for some legacy artefact, but it has the side effect
# of swallowing every `go.mod` in the monorepo. Without these negations,
# `actions/setup-go@v5` fails on CI with "go-version-file does not exist"
# because go.mod was never tracked. go.sum is already tracked (the rule
# only matched .mod), so we don't need to re-include it.
!go.mod
!**/go.mod

